title: Appointments to Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
					The Government announced today (November 25) the 
					re-appointment of five serving members and the appointment 
					of three new members to the Hospital Authority (HA), for a 
					two-year term with effect from December 1, 2016.  Mr William Chan Fu-keung, Mr Lester Garson Huang, Professor 
					Diana Lee Tze-fan, Mr Albert Wong Kwai-huen and Dr Lo

Wai-kwok have been re-appointed as members of the HA. The new members appointed are Ms Lisa Lau Man-man, Mr Daniel 
					Lam Chun and Mrs Ann Kung Yeung Yun-chi. Following are their 
					brief biographies: Ms Lau is a design consultant. She was the Chairman of the 
					Hong Kong Council on Smoking and Health. Ms Lau is currently 
					the Chairman of the Sir David Trench Fund Committee and a 
					member of the Action Committee Against Narcotics, the

member of the Action Committee Against Narcotics, the 
					Independent Police Complaints Council and the Sports 
					Commission.  Mr Lam is a veteran building surveyor, an expert in property 
					development and construction and a practising arbitrator. He 
					was the Director-Property of the Kowloon-Canton Railway 
					Corporation, the Deputy Chairman of the Board of the Urban 
					Renewal Authority and the Chairman of the Hong Kong

Renewal Authority and the Chairman of the Hong Kong 
					Institute of Arbitrators.  Mrs Kung is the Deputy Chief Executive of BOC Hong Kong 
					(Holdings) Limited. She is a member of the Standing 
					Committee on Directorate Salaries and Conditions of Service, 
					the Board of Ocean Park Corporation and the Board of 
					Directors of the Community Chest of Hong Kong; an elected 
					member of the General Committee and Chairman of the Banking

member of the General Committee and Chairman of the Banking 
					& Financial Services Group of the Employers' Federation of 
					Hong Kong; and a member of the Finance Management Committee 
					of the Hong Kong Management Association. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, welcomed 
					the three new members to the HA. He also thanked Ms Quince 
					Chong Wai-yan, Mr Ricky Fung Choi-cheung and Ms Winnie Ng, 
					who will retire from the HA with effect from December 1,

who will retire from the HA with effect from December 1, 2016, for their advice and contribution to the HA over the years. The HA, as from December 1, 2016, will comprise a chairman, 23 non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the Hospital Authority. Professor John Leong Chi-yan
